Yes 👍 I can guide you through it step by step.

Here’s how custom domains work with Netlify:

1. Choose & Buy a Domain

  • You’ll need to buy a domain name like kjtrev.com (or any you like).

  • You can buy it from providers like Namecheap, GoDaddy, Google Domains, Hostinger, etc. (around ₹500–₹800/year).

2. Connect the Domain to Netlify

Once you own the domain:

  1. Go to your site’s dashboard on Netlify.

  2. Click “Domain settings” → “Add custom domain”.

  3. Type in your domain (e.g., kjtrev.com).

  4. Netlify will give you DNS records (like CNAME and A records).

  5. Go to your domain provider’s dashboard (GoDaddy, Namecheap, etc.) and update the DNS to point to Netlify.

3. Automatic HTTPS

  • Netlify automatically provides a free SSL certificate from Let’s Encrypt.

  • Once DNS updates (can take a few hours), your site will be live at https://kjtrev.com. 🎤✨
